<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title><![CDATA[news - Sputnik News]]></title><link/> https://sputniknews.com/新闻<atom:link href="https://rsshub.app/sputniknews" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"></atom:link><description><![CDATA[news - Sputnik News - Made with love by RSSHub(https://github.com/DIYgod/RSSHub)]]></description><generator> RSSHub</generator><webmaster> i@diygod.me (DIY神)</webmaster><language> zh-cn</language><lastbuilddate> 2023 年 5 月 29 日星期一 15:24:04 GMT</lastbuilddate><ttl> 120 </ttl><item><title><![CDATA[What Are Anti-Drone Systems and How Do They Work?]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110774045" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/1d/1110772636_0:0:3201:2047_1440x900_80_0_1_f3d711cdd7a66da4f1081c731bc0f9e3.jpg?source-sid=rian_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1110772618" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230529/what-are-anti-drone-systems-and-how-do-they-work-1110774045.html?share-img=1110772618"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© Sputnik / Stringer</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">一名俄罗斯军人带着 DroneFall DF-6-2000 反无人机枪，在战斗位置，因为俄罗斯在乌克兰的军事行动仍在不明地点进行。</span> </div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="rian_photo" alt="A Russian serviceman with a DroneFall DF-6-2000 anti-drone gun, at combat position, as Russia's military operation in Ukraine continues, at an unknown location. - Sputnik International, 1920, 29.05.2023" title="一名俄罗斯军人带着 DroneFall DF-6-2000 反无人机枪，在战斗位置，因为俄罗斯在乌克兰的军事行动仍在继续，地点不明。" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/1d/1110772636_0:124:3201:1925_1920x0_80_0_0_4ab71ff9fc11b1b84437e06e2c6b9d9d.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/1d/1110772636_0:124:3201:1925_640x0_80_0_0_2b4937cfbc09234bc415f17f43fb0b5a.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/1d/1110772636_0:124:3201:1925_1280x0_80_0_0_6448baad8f229e5fae47c84ab159efdd.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/1d/1110772636_0:124:3201:1925_1920x0_80_0_0_4ab71ff9fc11b1b84437e06e2c6b9d9d.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © Sputnik / 斯特林格</div>/ </div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__author"><div class="article__author-item"><div class="article__author-wrapper"><div class="article__author-info"><div class="article__author-name">伊利亚楚卡诺夫</div><div class="article__author-links"> <a class="m-color-main" href="https://sputniknews.com/author_tsukanov_ilya/" title="所有材料">所有材料</a> <a data-modal-open="feedback_author" href="mailto:i.tsukanov@sputniknews.com" title="写给作者">写给作者</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">北约与俄罗斯在乌克兰的代理人冲突证明了无人机在现代战争中的重要性，双方都使用无人驾驶飞行器 (UAV) 进行侦察、瞄准和神风特攻队攻击。反无人机防御的四种主要类型是什么？各自的优点和缺点是什么？人造卫星探索。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> “未来的战争不会在战场或海上进行。他们将在太空中战斗，或者可能在一座非常高的山顶上进行战斗。无论哪种情况，大部分实际战斗都将由小型机器人完成，当你今天出发时，请永远记住——你的职责很明确：建造和维护这些机器人。”</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">这是 1997 年“辛普森一家”剧集“丽莎辛普森的秘密战争”中军事学校指挥官幽默但令人毛骨悚然的预测。四分之一个世纪后，在战争中使用无人机的想法变得无处不在，辛普森一家的喜剧效果永远被现实生活中的冲突所玷污。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">尽管自冷战以来就已经出现了装有胶卷相机的小型螺旋桨和火箭推进侦察<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230528/ukraine-loses-up-to-340-troops-near-donetsk---russian-military-1110655100.html" target="_blank">无人机</a>，但现代无人机战争，包括安装相机、遥控 GPS 的间谍和攻击无人机是 21 世纪初的产物， 2002 年，美国启动了<strong>世界上第一个</strong>使用无人机进行定点清除的行动。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">随着小型、廉价、现成的无人机<strong>在 2010 年代</strong>开始进入商业市场，它们开始被非国家行为者用来攻击军队和政府——美国支持的恐怖分子在<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230523/uks-sas-ran-secret-war-in-syria-since-2012---probe-1110546216.html" target="_blank">叙利亚对叙利亚的肮脏战争</a>中使用它们和俄罗斯军队，以及也门的胡塞武装分子部署他们对抗沙特领导的联盟。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">大型军用级无人机在 2020 年纳戈尔诺-卡拉巴赫阿塞拜疆和亚美尼亚志愿者之间的战争中发挥了作用，并且从 2022 年开始，北约支持的乌克兰军队在顿巴斯和整个乌克兰广泛部署以对抗俄罗斯军队。俄罗斯使用一系列国内开发的无人机防御系统来<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230526/watch-russian-tor-m1-weapon-system-obliterates-airborne-threats-in-ukraine-1110612794.html" target="_blank">对抗它们</a>。但更多关于下面的内容。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="h3"><h3 class="article__h2">无人机防御：有哪些类型？</h3></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> 20 世纪下半叶，苏联和美国将其防空和导弹防御研究的重点放在了大型、昂贵的有人驾驶战斗机、轰炸机、运输机以及弹道导弹和巡航导弹上。尽管这包括对奇幻概念的研究，包括在罗纳德里根的星球大战导弹防御计划下在太空中使用强大的激光，但其主要重点仍然是导弹——旨在拦截和摧毁敌机和导弹的火箭动力射弹。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="h3"><h3 class="article__h2">导弹可以用来击落无人机吗？</h3></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">对于足够大的无人机——包括像 Bayraktar TB2、General Atomics MQ-9 Reaper 或 Northrop Grumman RQ-4A Global Hawk 这样的无人机，它们的翼展分别为 12 米、20 米甚至 40 米，最有效的防御仍然是设计用于瞄准喷气式飞机的老式导弹。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">上个月，俄罗斯防空部队指挥官安德烈·德明报告说，在乌克兰的战斗中摧毁了 100 多架 Bayraktar 无人机。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “与美国全球鹰 (RQ-4) 或死神 (MQ-9) 或 Turkiye 的作战战术 Bayraktar-TB 等战略无人机作战与对载人飞机的反击之间几乎没有根本区别。德明在接受俄罗斯官方军报《红星报》采访时<a href="http://redstar.ru/ekzamen-derzhim-v-realnyh-boyah/?ysclid=lg9y22xoyp247132427" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">说</a>，在特别军事行动期间销毁了交付给乌克兰的 100 多架 Bayraktars，就是这方面的明显证据。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110774045" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230529/what-are-anti-drone-systems-and-how-do-they-work-1110774045.html?share-block=1110774057" data-title="“There are practically no fundamental distinctions between fighting against strategic drones like the US Global Hawk (RQ-4) or Reaper (MQ-9) or Turkiye’s operational-tactical Bayraktar-TB and counteraction to crewed aircraft. The elimination of more than 100 Bayraktars, delivered to Ukraine throughout the period of the special military operation, is clear evidence of this,” Demin said, speaking with Russia’s official army newspaper Krasnaya Zvezda."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="media"><div class="article__media"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="photo"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110774045" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/107819/38/1078193874_0:0:3147:2048_1440x900_80_0_1_b252ac271cd2356b24d3d9bbb3147ae2.jpg?source-sid=rian_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1078193872" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230529/what-are-anti-drone-systems-and-how-do-they-work-1110774045.html?share-img=1078193872"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© Sputnik / Алексей Куденко</span> <span class="photoview__desc-text">Buk-M2 导弹系统在胜利日夜间阅兵式上在莫斯科阅兵。档案照片。</span> </div></noindex><img media-type="photo" data-source-sid="rian_photo" alt="Night-time repetition of the Buk-M2 missile system in Moscow. - Sputnik International, 1920, 29.05.2023" title="莫斯科 Buk-M2 导弹系统的夜间重复。" class=" lazyload" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/107819/38/1078193874_0:0:3147:2048_1920x0_80_0_0_84b73770768d8ed633a3c358a2961dc5.jpg" srcset="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22%20width=%221920%22%20height=%221249%22%3E%3C/svg%3E 100w" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1249" data-srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/107819/38/1078193874_0:0:3147:2048_640x0_80_0_0_692413932371e1febfa90d92794c9198.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/107819/38/1078193874_0:0:3147:2048_1280x0_80_0_0_21f5dd1ef2cd1d3e254fe12dd14dc231.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/107819/38/1078193874_0:0:3147:2048_1920x0_80_0_0_84b73770768d8ed633a3c358a2961dc5.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__description " data-nosnippet=""> Buk-M2 导弹系统在胜利日阅兵的夜间重演期间在莫斯科阅兵。档案照片。 </div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © Sputnik / Алексей Куденко</div> /</div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">为了<strong>对抗大型无人机</strong>，包括探测和摧毁它们，可以使用与传统飞机相同的监控和打击系统。这不仅在乌克兰得到证明，2019 年 6 月在霍尔木兹海峡的伊朗领空击落了一架价值 2.2 亿美元的全球鹰，这架全球鹰由美国海军运营，由伊朗公路机动防空系统称为 3rd Khordad。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="h3"><h3 class="article__h2">如何使用电子对抗来摧毁无人机？</h3></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> Demin 承认，较小的无人机，包括所谓的微型和微型无人机，更难被发现，并指出这些武器的“小有效反射面”用于雷达探测，并表示使用标准雷达设备跟踪此类系统并揭示它们的轨迹是“相当有问题的”。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">为此，俄罗斯军方开发了一种不同类型的防空系统<strong>——RLK-MTs Valdai</strong> ，这是一种专用雷达，专门用于探测、压制和压制雷达横截面极低的小型无人机。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> RLK-MT 由<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230529/watch-russias-buk-missile-system-in-action-during-special-op-1110760533.html" target="_blank">Buk</a>和 S-300/S-400/S-500 系列防空和导弹防御系统的制造商 Almaz-Antey 开发，是一种车载雷达综合体，旨在探测最远距离的敌方无人机15 公里，并在 2 公里或更短的近距离范围内使用电子对抗措施（使用控制和导航信号抑制模块）将其击落。该综合体的检测系统包括一个 X 波段雷达模块、热成像仪和摄像机、一个无线电信号源探测器模块。这些车辆可以远程操作。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="media"><div class="article__media"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="photo"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110774045" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/1d/1110773633_0:0:800:532_1440x900_80_0_1_b5f21ca8b90e4cbfff14670f4468540b.jpg?source-sid=not_sputnik_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1110773615" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230529/what-are-anti-drone-systems-and-how-do-they-work-1110774045.html?share-img=1110773615"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© 照片：Almaz-Antei</span> <span class="photoview__desc-text">RLK-MTs Valdai，一种特殊用途的俄罗斯雷达系统，专门设计用于探测、抑制和压制雷达横截面极低的小型无人机。</span> </div></noindex><img media-type="photo" data-source-sid="not_sputnik_photo" alt="The RLK-MTs Valdai, a special-purpose Russian radar system designed specifically to detect, suppress and neutralize small drones with extremely low radar cross sections.  - Sputnik International, 1920, 29.05.2023" title="RLK-MTs Valdai，一种特殊用途的俄罗斯雷达系统，专门设计用于探测、抑制和压制雷达横截面极低的小型无人机。" class=" lazyload" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/1d/1110773633_0:0:800:532_1920x0_80_0_0_9432a74e7a0270dc7a04bbde2a22fe52.jpg" srcset="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22%20width=%221920%22%20height=%221277%22%3E%3C/svg%3E 100w" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1277" data-srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/1d/1110773633_0:0:800:532_640x0_80_0_0_358508e57e8e93fc91d12a340c46d269.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/1d/1110773633_0:0:800:532_1280x0_80_0_0_5065f3f230861f56222853d602c17411.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/1d/1110773633_0:0:800:532_1920x0_80_0_0_9432a74e7a0270dc7a04bbde2a22fe52.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__description " data-nosnippet=""> RLK-MTs Valdai，一种特殊用途的俄罗斯雷达系统，专门设计用于探测、抑制和压制雷达横截面极低的小型无人机。 </div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © 照片 : Almaz-Antei </div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">德明证实，RLK-MT“已经在执行作战任务，以覆盖关键的军事和国家设施，包括那些在特别军事行动区的设施”，并表示他预计未来几年该系统的产量将大幅增加。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">装有检测系统和强大电子对抗措施的大型车载系统可以说是抵御小型无人机的最有效防御手段，但肯定不是唯一的。几家俄罗斯制造商已经创建了更小的系统，<a href="https://antidrone.kaspersky.com/en/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">从</a>商业和工业反无人机监控和抑制硬件到军用级便携式反无人机步枪。这些武器<a href="https://iz.ru/1502247/2023-04-21/v-rossii-sozdali-protivodronovoe-ruzhe-pars-s-stepashka" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">包括</a><strong>PARS-S Stepashka——</strong>一种重 9.6 公斤的反无人机枪，能够劫持敌方无人机并迫使它们降落或返回发射场。该系统在 500 米至 1.5 公里范围内有效。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">其他类似的便携式反无人机系统也出现在战场的镜头中，包括<strong>Stupor</strong>电磁步枪——它使用电磁脉冲抑制无人机的控制通道并迫使它们坠落。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="social"><div class="ria-tweet"><blockquote class="twitter-tweet"><p lang="en" dir="ltr">反无人机枪的工作原理（俄罗斯国防部的视频）<br><br>俄罗斯空降部队在乌克兰特别军事行动期间积极使用反无人机枪<a href="https://t.co/5GCPZTEpn1">pic.twitter.com/5GCPZTEpn1</a></p> -人造卫星 (@SputnikInt) <a href="https://twitter.com/SputnikInt/status/1663194212291018752?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">2023 年 5 月 29 日</a></blockquote></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="h3"><h3 class="article__h2">激光如何对抗无人机？</h3></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">激光脉冲武器的进步增强了它们在现代战争中的应用前景。去年，负责国防和航天工业的前俄罗斯副总理尤里·鲍里索夫 (Yuri Borisov) <a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20220518/russia-tests-combat-laser-capable-of-burning-drones-at-distance-of-some-3-miles-official-says-1095598028.html" target="_blank">透露</a>，俄罗斯军方已经测试了一种名为<strong>Zadira</strong>的神秘战斗激光系统，该系统能够在几秒钟内远距离焚烧无人机在乌克兰最多 5 公里。它的开发始于 2016 年，在 Rosatom 的子公司俄罗斯联邦核中心的支持下。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="vrez"><div class="article__vrez"><div class="article__vrez-text"><p>不要将 Zadira 与<strong>Peresvet</strong>相混淆——Peresvet 是一种战略激光武器，旨在瞄准位于核电站上方 1,500 公里轨道上的敌人。该系统于 2018 年 12 月进入战斗任务测试，但尚未在乌克兰使用。</p></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">俄罗斯并不是唯一一个尝试使用激光武器进行反无人机战争的国家，美国和以色列<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20220712/israel-hopes-to-wow-biden-with-iron-beam-iron-dome-davids-sling-missile-show-and-tell-1097239635.html" target="_blank">也在研发</a>此类武器。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">与传统防空导弹相比，激光有几个明显的优势——包括成本低（例如，以色列官员吹嘘说，新的<strong>Iron Beam</strong>激光防空系统仅使用价值 2 美元的电力——比传统防空导弹<strong>低 10,000-50,000 倍</strong>铁穹导弹）。但激光也有<strong>许多缺点</strong>，包括需要确保大量电力（限制其移动性），以及在某些天气条件下（包括雾和云层）操作的问题。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="h3"><h3 class="article__h2">无人机可以用来对抗其他无人机吗？</h3></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">最后但同样重要的是，在便携式反无人机防御系统列表中还有其他无人机。 <strong>ZALA 柳叶刀</strong>多用途游荡弹药/神风敢死队无人机等系统能够瞄准敌方无人机，其开发人员创造了一个他们称之为“空中采矿”的概念，涉及在前线区域部署大量柳叶刀以防止重型攻击无人机的入侵。当敌方无人机接近时，“柳叶刀”锁定敌方目标并<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230515/what-is-the-lancet-kamikaze-drone-and-what-makes-it-so-deadly-1110378634.html" target="_blank">高速俯冲，</a>迫使其脱离天空。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="h3"><h3 class="article__h2">俄罗斯的反无人机战争有多成功？</h3></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">自从俄罗斯卷入乌克兰危机以来，它已经做出了<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230429/skys-the-limit-for-russias-drone-industry--heres-why-1109951680.html">许多艰难但必要的改变</a>，为陆军提供有效无人机作战所需的装备。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">上周，英国国防部的一项非机密情报评估得出的<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230521/uk-military-attributes-success-of-russian-strikes-deep-into-ukraine-to-improved-use-of-spy-drones-1110507133.html" target="_blank">结论是</a>，俄罗斯军方已<strong>成功地将无人机侦察整合</strong>到乌克兰腹地的远程导弹袭击行动中。同样在上周，英国皇家联合服务研究所的另一份报告<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230524/advanced-russian-ew-systems-reportedly-take-out-10000-ukrainian-drones-per-month--1110553449.html" target="_blank">计算出</a>，俄罗斯一直在使用电子战能力<strong>每月摧毁超过 10,000 架乌克兰无人机</strong>。根据评估，俄罗斯在整个 1,200 公里的前线沿线“大约每 6 英里（9.6 公里）就有一个大型电子战系统”。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="social" data-social="telegram"><div class="article__tg"></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">这些评估呼应了乌克兰国防部一位内部人士的抱怨，他在 3 月份告诉一家西方媒体，俄罗斯军队已经获得了针对乌克兰庞大的北约无人机库的<a href="https://www.economist.com/europe/2023/03/20/ukraine-is-betting-on-drones-to-strike-deep-into-russia" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">“黑魔法”</a>能力，包括“干扰频率、欺骗 GPS、 [并且] 将无人机发送到错误的高度，这样它就会从天上掉下来。”</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 29 May 2023 15:02:16 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230529/what-are-anti-drone-systems-and-how-do-they-work-1110774045.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230529/what-are-anti-drone-systems-and-how-do-they-work-1110774045.html<category>军队</category><category>安德烈德明</category><category>乌克兰</category><category>俄罗斯</category><category>北约</category><category>柳叶刀</category><category>拜拉克塔</category><category>无人机</category><category>无人机</category><category>无人驾驶的航空机</category><category>俄罗斯军队</category><category>乌克兰武装部队</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[World's Deep Ocean is Gasping for Breath Amid Loss of Oxygen, Study Warns]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110774963" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/1d/1110774542_0:0:3216:2048_1440x900_80_0_1_e1bc6d58c2b8ea2f480fbc152d7f9cc3.jpg?source-sid=afp" data-photoview-image-id="1110774524" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230529/worlds-deep-ocean-is-gasping-for-breath-amid-loss-of-oxygen-study-warns-1110774963.html?share-img=1110774524"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© <a href="https://ria.ru/docs/about/copyright_afp.html" title="法新社 2023">AFP 2023</a> / TORSTEN BLACKWOOD</span> <span class="photoview__desc-text">2008 年 1 月 11 日，一座巨大的冰山 (R) 从澳大利亚南极领地的诺克斯海岸断裂。</span> </div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="afp" alt="An enormous iceberg (R) breaks off the Knox Coast in the Australian Antarctic Territory on January 11, 2008.  - Sputnik International, 1920, 29.05.2023" title="2008 年 1 月 11 日，一座巨大的冰山 (R) 从澳大利亚南极领地的诺克斯海岸断裂。" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/1d/1110774542_0:120:3216:1929_1920x0_80_0_0_89f0ab3a9a65fdfd6efb28e6e83bef8c.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/1d/1110774542_0:120:3216:1929_640x0_80_0_0_90c70775a34aed491b9a8e775410524d.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/1d/1110774542_0:120:3216:1929_1280x0_80_0_0_c6c25123df9d8c9129e9fbf94afefff2.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/1d/1110774542_0:120:3216:1929_1920x0_80_0_0_89f0ab3a9a65fdfd6efb28e6e83bef8c.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © <a href="https://ria.ru/docs/about/copyright_afp.html" title="法新社 2023">AFP 2023</a> / TORSTEN BLACKWOOD </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__author"><div class="article__author-item"><div class="article__author-wrapper"><div class="article__author-info"><div class="article__author-name">斯韦特兰娜·埃基缅科</div><div class="article__author-links"><a class="m-color-main" href="https://sputniknews.com/author_svetlana_ekimenko/" title="所有材料">所有材料</a> <a data-modal-open="feedback_author" href="mailto:s.ekimenko@sputniknews.com" title="写给作者">写给作者</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">由于南极洲的环境对地球产生巨大影响，从影响气候到生活的各个方面，澳大利亚研究人员最近的一项发现得出了令人震惊的结论。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">澳大利亚科学家的一项新研究表明，南极海洋深处的氧气含量正在以比预期更快的速度下降。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">随着南极冰盖<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230216/doomsday-glacier-rapidly-shedding-ice--we-should-all-be-very-concerned-study-warns-1107505852.html" target="_blank">在气候变暖的情况下融化，</a>坏消息是<strong>大量含盐、富氧水的下沉速度已经放缓</strong>。<strong>由于冰川融化，地表水变得不那么咸，它们变得更加浮力</strong>。这极大地影响了一个至关重要的过程，即用氧气补充深海，发表在<em>《自然气候变化》</em>杂志上的研究结果表明<em>。</em></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">当含有氧气的浓水下沉时，它会变成科学家所说的<em>南极底水</em>(AABW)。<em>联邦科学与工业研究组织</em>(CSIRO) 的团队解释说，这个过程可以被描述为将氧气“泵入”太平洋、大西洋和印度洋<em>。</em></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">领导这项研究的 Kathy Gunn 博士和她的团队使用了一种新开发的方法来测量南极海洋（也称为南大洋）的深层环流。他们将观测数据与模型模拟相结合。除了船只的观察外，还考虑了通过固定在海底的电线上的仪器测量的水速、温度和盐度。 <a href="https://www.nature.com/articles/s41558-023-01667-8" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">该研究称</a>，这些工具最多可保留两年。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">当研究人员计算 AABW 的体积和氧气输送时，他们将注意力集中在巨大的变化上。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"><p> “我们的观察显示，自 1990 年代以来，南极洲周围的深海环流整体放缓了约 30%。这种放缓锁定了数十年的影响，”Kathy Gunn 博士说。 </p></div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110774963" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230529/worlds-deep-ocean-is-gasping-for-breath-amid-loss-of-oxygen-study-warns-1110774963.html?share-block=1110774969" data-title="“Our observations show the deep ocean circulation around Antarctica has slowed overall by about 30 per cent since the 1990s. This slowdown locks in decades of impacts,&amp;quot; Dr. Kathy Gunn stated."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">虽然之前的模型预测到 2050 年 AABW 环流可能会放缓 40% 以上，但现在，新的研究结果表明，预计的放缓比预期来得更早，该研究的合著者、澳大利亚气象局副主任马修英格兰教授解释说南极科学卓越中心。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">这一过程的重要后果之一是环流减慢使海底停滞不前。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> Matthew England 补充说：“这会将营养物质困在深海中，减少可用于支持海洋表面附近海洋生物的营养物质。” </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110774963" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230529/worlds-deep-ocean-is-gasping-for-breath-amid-loss-of-oxygen-study-warns-1110774963.html?share-block=1110775150" data-title="&quot;This would trap nutrients in the deep ocean, reducing the nutrients available to support marine life near the ocean surface,&quot; Matthew England added."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">另一位合著者 Steve Rintoul 博士解释说，与南极冰盖融化导致的海平面上升相关的典型研究结果相比，这项研究的结果强调了更多的担忧。研究小组警告说，记录到的氧气水平总体下降正在<strong>改变深海的结构和化学性质</strong>，这表明这可能在未来几年产生深远的影响。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 29 May 2023 14:31:10 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230529/worlds-deep-ocean-is-gasping-for-breath-amid-loss-of-oxygen-study-warns-1110774963.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230529/worlds-deep-ocean-is-gasping-for-breath-amid-loss-of-oxygen-study-warns-1110774963.html<category>超越政治</category><category>科学与技术</category><category>海洋</category><category>氧</category><category>南极洋</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Danish Parliament to Consider Civil Proposal to Legalize Euthanasia - Reports]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110776126" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/105807/54/1058075446_0:0:2048:1365_1440x900_80_0_1_9d8d552449eb4b6e0636b2633f26383f.jpg?source-sid=cc_by-sa_20" data-photoview-image-id="1058075445" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230529/danish-parliament-to-consider-civil-proposal-to-legalize-euthanasia---reports-1110776126.html?share-img=1058075445"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright"><a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/2.0/" title="CC BY-SA 2.0">CC BY-SA 2.0</a> / <a href="https://www.flickr.com/photos/126396110@N06/" title="阿尔贝托比斯卡尔金">Alberto Biscalchin</a> /<a href="https://www.flickr.com/photos/126396110@N06/26137241265/" title="安乐死">安乐死</a></span><span class="photoview__desc-text">安乐死</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="cc_by-sa_20" alt="Euthanasia - Sputnik International, 1920, 29.05.2023" title="安乐死" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/105807/54/1058075446_0:107:2048:1259_1920x0_80_0_0_74521db533038af1b14d4827834bb8fa.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/105807/54/1058075446_0:107:2048:1259_640x0_80_0_0_45ffdbdbe718d033d52cc04d4985f24f.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/105807/54/1058075446_0:107:2048:1259_1280x0_80_0_0_c3d9d00545255debd71041f72e624345.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/105807/54/1058075446_0:107:2048:1259_1920x0_80_0_0_74521db533038af1b14d4827834bb8fa.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/2.0/" title="CC BY-SA 2.0">CC BY-SA 2.0</a> / <a href="https://www.flickr.com/photos/126396110@N06/" title="阿尔贝托比斯卡尔金">Alberto Biscalchin</a> /<a href="https://www.flickr.com/photos/126396110@N06/26137241265/" title="安乐死">安乐死</a></div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">据莫斯科（人造卫星）网报道：丹麦媒体周一报道，一份要求丹麦安乐死合法化的民事请愿书已有 50,000 多人签署，超过了议会开始审议该提案所需的最低签名人数。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">报告称，丹麦医学协会 (DADL) 反对该倡议，称政府应增加对姑息治疗的投资。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “这有很多原因：我们认为痛苦不应该通过杀人来解决；我们害怕我们在引入安乐死的国家看到的滑坡；我们认为人们应该投资于适当的终结-生命姑息治疗，”该协会伦理委员会主席克劳斯·克劳森(Klaus Klausen)被媒体引述说。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110776126" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230529/danish-parliament-to-consider-civil-proposal-to-legalize-euthanasia---reports-1110776126.html?share-block=1110776128" data-title="&quot;There are many reasons for this: we do not think that suffering should be managed by killing people; we are afraid of the slippery slope we see in countries where euthanasia has been brought in; and we think one should invest in proper end-of-life palliative care,&quot; Klaus Klausen, chairman of the association's ethics committee, was quoted as saying by the media outlet. "></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">该提议是由一名卫生工作者提出的<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20191106/nearly-half-of-norwegian-church-members-support-euthanasia-1077234204.html" target="_blank">，他遇到了希望被允许死亡的患者</a>。议会将首次审议该提案。 2018 年，该倡议收到了 8,386 个签名，2019 年收到了 1,409 个签名。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">到目前为止，在欧洲，瑞士、 <a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20201217/bill-legalising-euthanasia-approved-by-spains-lower-house-of-parliament-1081493309.html" target="_blank">西班牙</a>、比利时、 <a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20181112/netherlands-euthanasia-cases-1069732305.html" target="_blank">荷兰</a>和卢森堡允许安乐死。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 29 May 2023 14:28:42 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230529/danish-parliament-to-consider-civil-proposal-to-legalize-euthanasia---reports-1110776126.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230529/danish-parliament-to-consider-civil-proposal-to-legalize-euthanasia---reports-1110776126.html<category>世界</category><category>丹麦</category><category>安乐死</category><category>合法化</category></item></channel></rss>